  "cloudDescCirrocumulus":"Cirrocumulus clouds belong to high-level clouds. They appear white and shiny, forming thin scale-like patterns that are often arranged in rows or groups.",
  "cloudDescAltostratus":"Altostratus clouds belong to middle-level clouds. They have a thick cloud layer that often covers the sky. Sunlight can pass through them but usually without producing a halo.",
